        Adrian Rosebrock June 2, 2015 at 6:41 am #

        Hi Alex ‚Äî thanks so much, I‚Äôm glad you enjoyed the post!

        So in general, the solution to your surveillance system will depend on (1) what gives you the best results, and (2) how complicated you want to make it. Using HOG requires training your own custom object detector which can non-trivial, especially if you are just getting started in computer vision and machine learning. Furthermore, this classifier would only really work to detect what you trained it to detect ‚Äî it wouldn‚Äôt be able to detect true ‚Äúmotion‚Äù for arbitrary objects in a video stream.

        That said, I think you‚Äôre on the right track. You want to use some basic motion detection, followed by more advanced methods for tracking the bounding box. I don‚Äôt think dlib‚Äôs correlation tracker has Python bindings, but I know this one for OpenCV does.
