    Reply
        Adrian Rosebrock November 16, 2016 at 1:46 pm #

        If a person doesn‚Äôt move or moves really slowly then eventually this method will ‚Äúaverage‚Äù them out of the detection. In this case, you need to tune Line 76 , specifically the alpha weight parameter. Once you‚Äôve detected a person you might want to try using correlation tracking or CamShift to track them.

        As for the number of regions in an image that can contain motion, it‚Äôs simply: len(cnts)
